		"description": "<p><em>Requires attunement by a creature wearing the sword's scabbard</em></p><p>This double-sided blade is made of red-hued iron and is engraved with Draconic runes that glow crimson when near a true dragon. The hilt is made of blackened iron and wrapped with red silver wire, the pommel shaped like the head of a red dragon.</p><p>This family greatsword is the property of Lord Pemberton. The scabbard was lost decades ago in Brockendale Castle when the Pembertons&rsquo; ancestors fled. Since then most believe it to be a family legend&mdash;a colorful story, but nothing more.</p><p>You gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this greatsword. When used against a dragon, you instead gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls, and deal an extra 3d6 slashing damage. When the blade scores a critical hit against a dragon, the dragon head on its pommel glows with fury, dealing an extra 3d10 radiant damage.</p><p>Additionally, you have advantage on saving throws made to resist the attacks and traits of dragons (including breath weapons, roars, and even spells if a dragon can cast them).</p>",
